r treatment for T3 N0 disease. But sch patients were included in Rapido as well.'),(1113,429630800,NULL,'We had a long discussion about GOC. He has a recently treated HN cancer an untreated lung cancer new cardiac issues and his age givne these consideration I would be cautious to rescusitate him - as there is a high risk of him requiring prolongued ICU with minimal potnetial for meaningful recovery and givne his multiple cancers including one untreated this would leave him to die slowly from his cancer. Given this situation I doubt that ICU would accept him However despite this he still hopes that he could be resusciated sucessfuly. He wishes t be R1 despite my reccomendatiin for M1.'),(1114,429630800,NULL,'I am very worried about his chest pain, SOB, inability to walk distances - this precludes SBRT to the lung at this time. I will call himback in 4 weeks to evaluate his situation. Although this is suboptimal he is in no shape for SBRT lung at this time.'),(1115,888335110,2,'urgently. I deferred discussion about systemic therapy until we have more info.'),(1116,309094700,6,'The patient lives in red deer and cannot easily travel to Calgary for treatment. I offered him urgent treatment here - and he says that he cannot easily get here. He has no supports for treatment here.     His case was sent from CACC to TBCC seeking expert therapy opinion from the HN or GI group. I emphasize that this is an esophageal cancer and can be treated with palliative intent.'),(1117,907170390,3,'He understands that we will proceed with clinical trial of systemic therapy first reserving RT depending on his response.'),(1118,316203421,9,'We spoke about her main vlaues of finding peace, being with her family. She understands that radiation will not prolong her life significantly andthere are significant side effects. This is NOT in keeping with her values. I strongly advise hospice and best supportive care.'),(1119,624527121,1,'seg 5 area shows subtle progression. This has been very small